data.text:
His Majesty King Fuad II of Egypt is pleased to announce the engagement of his eldest His Royal Highness Prince Mohammed Ali, Prince of Said son, and Her Royal Highness Princess Noal Zaher, daughter of His Royal Highness Prince Daud Pashtunyar Zaher and Her Royal Highness Princess Fatima Zaher Aref, from a younger branch of the royal family of Afghanistan branch. Prince Pashtunyar Daud Khan was the seventh child of His Majesty the late King Mohammed Zahir Shah of Afghanistan and Her Majesty Queen Humaira Begum.

The engagement was celebrated on April 27 in Istanbul. Princess Noal Zaher was born in Rome. There she studied at St. Dominic Institute before obtaining a degree in European Business London and go in the same city, Webster University. She designs and creates jewelry. Said the prince was born in Cairo February 5, 1979 and was educated at Le Rosey. It is real estate expert. The mother of Princess Noal and his brother, His Royal Highness Prince Doran Daud, had wanted to be present, as well as His Majesty King Fouad and TRH Prince Fakhr Eddin and Princess Fawzia Latifa, brother and sister of the groom. A marriage that unites the royal families of Egypt and Afghanistan.
